simple habits for healthy hormones 🌞

1) The circadian rhythm influences our hormonal rhythms! Prioritizing sleep has greatly improved my wellbeing 💛

2) Pairing fruits with fats can better regulate your blood sugar (and who doesn’t love a yogurt parfait 🍓).

3) Quality supplementation! I love that @perelelhealth supports you in whatever phase of your journey you’re in— PCOS support, your first trimester, you name it. For us, that’s conception ❤️ Their conception support pack contains antioxidant support, added omegas, additional folate and a full-spectrum prenatal vitamin to prepare my body for pregnancy (when that time comes!). & I love knowing that they’re OB/GYN founded, you can use my code MRG20 for 20% off your first order! #perelelpartner 

4) Lower intensity workouts can protect the adrenals and balance hormones! 

5) Stress can wreak havoc on your body’s natural hormone balance…

6) You simply cannot do it all. Give yourself time alone to relax & recharge as needed 🌟

.
.
.

new beginnings… 🥹🏡🤸🏼‍♂️💫💭
the best is yet to come 🤍
baby is a… 🥹🤍

Our baby BOY 💙 

What a sweet season this has been— one so evident of God’s divine hand in it all. Week by week, reading about baby’s developments—  he has a heartbeat, now hair follicles, ears, unique fingerprints. He’s the size of a grape, now a pear, a cucumber. My anticipation of laying to rest, knowing I’ll feel his tiny kicks. 

I think about the perfect timing of 9 months to prepare. What color should the nursery be? Where will he be born? Is my body ready? Are WE ready? Worry and doubt easily creep in. Will he be safe? Will we be good parents? 

But then I remember Psalm 34:4-5, “I sought the Lord, and he answered me and delivered me from all my fears. Those who look to him are radiant, and their faces shall never be ashamed.” A verse I read every morning in the library, remembering to seek Him each day throughout college. A verse I still read every morning, remembering to seek Him throughout my journey of motherhood. We are so grateful for it all… my cup runneth over 🤍

easy weekend getaway idea, just outside of Austin 🏕️🪵🌠🍃🥾

Aidan & I love our weekend road-trips, Texas has SO much to see 🌼 but did you know, distracted driving accounts for one in five traffic crashes in Texas? always remember to pre-select your playlist before driving, put your phone on do not disturb mode, and pull off the road entirely and come to a complete stop before talking or texting… so you can make it to your destination safely & enjoy some R&R! 💫 @txdot #EndTheStreakTX #HeadsUpTexas #ad
